深圳野生动物禁食条例征求意见 这些动物被明确列入禁食黑名单…… 。
Shenzhen Wild Animal Fasting Code for comments These animals are on a list of banned animals...
于惠如2020-02-26 15:02。
In favour: 2020-02-26 15: 02.
扫描二维码分享到朋友圈。
Scanning two-dimensional code to share with friends.
经济观察网 记者 于惠如2月25日晚，深圳市人大常委会官方网站发布关于《深圳经济特区全面禁止食用野生动物条例（草案征求意见稿）》（以下简称：《征求意见稿》）公开征求意见的公告。
On the evening of February 25, the official website of the Standing Committee of the Standing Committee of the Shenzhen Municipal People's Congress (NPCSC) issued a notice of public consultation on the draft Shenzhen Special Economic Zone Regulations on the Prohibition of Consumption of Wild Animals (draft Exposure Draft).
其中，列明了禁食野生动物、可食动物名单，同时，还明确了对各类违法行为的具体罚则。
Among them, the list of fasting wild animals and edible animals is listed, and the specific penalties for various kinds of illegal acts are also specified.
。
.
人工繁育、饲养陆生野生动物纳入“禁食”范围。
Artificial breeding and raising of terrestrial wildlife are included in the scope of the fast.
《征求意见稿》明确，将保护类野生动物和非保护类陆生野生动物以及人工繁育、饲养的陆生野生动物均纳入禁止食用范围。
The exposure draft makes it clear that the protection of wild animals and non-protected terrestrial wildlife, as well as artificial breeding and breeding of terrestrial wildlife are prohibited.
。
.
对此，深圳市人大常委会法工委解读表示，不管保护类野生动物还是其他非保护类陆生野生动物，都具有容易携带和传播疫病的风险，只有将所有野外环境下自然生长繁殖的陆生野生动物全面纳入禁止食用的范围，才能有效减少人与野生动物的不适当接触。
In response, the Standing Committee of the Shenzhen Municipal People's Congress interpreted it as saying that the protection of wild animals and other non-protected terrestrial wildlife carries a high risk of carrying and spreading disease.
。
.
对于人工繁育的野生动物，深圳市人大常委会法工委称，其本身就违背了野生动物自然生长规律，且目前人工繁育野生动物的监管体系尚不健全，检验检疫标准和手段无法满足人工繁育的野生动物作为食品的防疫要求，监管部门在执法中也难以分辨野生动物是野外捕获的还是人工繁育的。
As for artificially propagated wild animals, the Standing Committee of the Standing Committee of the Shenzhen Municipal People's Congress said it was itself against the natural growth of wild animals and that the current regulatory system for artificially breeding wild animals is inadequate.
此外，人类长期以来有喂养猫狗等动物作为宠物的习惯，宠物与人类建立起比其他动物更为亲近的关系，禁止食用宠物动物是人类文明的共识，宠物也应当列入禁止食用的范围。
In addition, humans have long had the habit of feeding animals such as cats and dogs as pets. Pets have developed a closer relationship with humans than other animals.
。
.
同时，由于供科研实验的动物有其特殊的饲养目的和饲养方法，也不适宜食用，应当排除在可食用范围之外。
At the same time, animals for scientific experiments, because of their special breeding purposes and breeding methods, are not fit for consumption and should be excluded from the range of edible goods.
。
.
龟、甲鱼、蛇、鸟、昆虫被列入黑名单。
Turtles, turtles, snakes, birds and insects are blacklisted.
《意见征求稿》明确列出了可食动物名单及禁食黑名单。
The RFI specified the list of edible animals and the blacklist of fasting.
。
.
其中，可食动物及其制品包括：猪、牛、羊、驴、兔、鸡、鸭、鹅、鸽以及深圳市人民政府决定可以食用的其他家禽家畜；依照法律、法规未禁止食用的水生动物。
Among them, edible animals and their products include pigs, cows, sheep, donkeys, rabbits, chickens, ducks, geese, pigeons and other domestic animals that the people's government of Shenzhen may decide to eat; and aquatic animals not prohibited by law or regulations.
。
.
此外，因蜂蜜、燕窝、雪蛤等动物相关衍生物已经被公众广泛接受，并具有较为成熟的检验检疫标准，《征求意见稿》不禁止食用蜂蜜、燕窝、雪蛤等动物衍生物。
In addition, since honey, bird's nest, snow clam and other animal-related derivatives have been widely accepted by the public, and have more mature inspection and quarantine standards, the Exposure Draft does not prohibit the consumption of animal derivatives such as honey, bird's nest and snow clam.
。
.
对于社会比较关注的经人工繁育、饲养的龟、甲鱼、蛇、鸟、昆虫等野生动物，也具有不小的疫病传播风险，无法保证食用的安全性，为此将被排除在可食用动物范围之外。
As for the wild animals, such as turtles, turtles, snakes, birds and insects, which are of great concern to the society, there is not little risk of spreading the disease.
。
.
深圳市人大常委会法工委表示，通过市场调查，《征求意见稿》所列的九种可食用陆生动物和未禁止食用的水生动物已涵盖了深圳食品交易、餐饮市场上的主要动物品种，足以满足人民群众生活需要，符合大多数深圳市民的饮食习惯，不会对市民的日常饮食带来大的影响。
Through market research, the nine edible terrestrial animals and non-edible aquatic animals listed in the Exposure Draft cover the main animal species on the Shenzhen food trade and catering market, enough to satisfy the people's living needs and meet the dietary habits of most Shenzhen residents, according to the Standing Committee of the Shenzhen Municipal Peoples Congress.
。
.
同时，深圳市人大常委会法工委称，《征求意见稿》也在明确规定常见的九种可食用陆生动物以及水生动物的基础上，授权市人民政府根据国家后续出台的规定，并结合深圳实际，补充制定其他可以食用的家禽家畜目录，以进一步满足人民群众的生活需要。
Meanwhile, the Standing Committee of the Standing Committee of the Shenzhen Municipal People's Congress said that the exposure draft also authorized the municipal people's government to make additional catalogues of edible poultry and livestock in accordance with the regulations promulgated by the state and taking into account the actual conditions in Shenzhen, so as to further meet the needs of the people.
。
.
食用禁食动物每人1000元起罚。
Food fasting animals start at 1000 yuan per person.
针对实用、饲养、经营野生动物及其制品的行为，《征求意见稿》也明确了具体的罚则。
The exposure draft also specifies specific penalties for the use, raising and trading of wildlife and their products.
。
.
任何组织和个人不得以提供食用为目的饲养禁止食用的动物、不得以提供食用为目的生产经营禁止食用的动物及其制品、不得为相关生产经营行为提供场所或者服务。
No organization or individual may keep animals whose consumption is prohibited for the purpose of providing them with food, or produce or deal in animals and their products the consumption of which is prohibited for the purpose of providing food, or provide places or services for relevant production and business operations.
同时，不得以药膳的名义食用或者生产经营禁止食用的动物及其制品，禁止宣传、诱导食用等行为。
At the same time, animals and their products the consumption of which is prohibited shall not be eaten or produced or handled in the name of medicinal food.
。
.
食用法律、法规规定保护的野生动物及其制品的，对食用人每人处二千元以上二万元以下罚款，对组织食用者处一万元以上五万元以下罚款。
Anyone who eats wildlife and its products protected by laws or regulations shall be fined from 2,000 yuan to 20,000 yuan per person and from 10,000 yuan to 50,000 yuan for the edible part of the organization.
食用法律、法规规定保护的野生动物以外其他禁止食用的动物及其制品的，对食用人每人处一千元以上二千元以下罚款，对组织食用者处五千元以上一万元以下罚款。
Whoever eats any animal or animal products the consumption of which is prohibited by law or regulations shall be fined from 1,000 to 2,000 yuan per person and from 5,000 to 10,000 yuan for the edible part of the organization.
。
.
此外，《征求意见稿》对生产经营野生动物、禁食动物，以提供食用为目的生产经营禁止食用的动物及其制品的行为均给予不同程度的金额处罚。
In addition, the exposure draft imposes various monetary penalties on the production and marketing of wildlife and fasting animals, as well as on the production and operation of animals and their products prohibited for consumption for the purpose of providing food.
情节严重的，依法吊销相关许可证，构成犯罪的，依法追究刑事责任。
If the circumstances are serious, the relevant license shall be revoked according to law.
。
.
深圳市人大常委会法工委表示，通过立法禁止私宰和相关交易，禁止以提供食用为目的的陆生动物活体销售，实行标准化冷链配送供应，一方面能够在提升生鲜动物食品质量安全水平的同时减少野生动物与人类的不适当接触，有效防控疫病传播，另一方面也可以防止将野生动物通过农贸市场、超市、餐馆、酒楼等端上餐桌。
The Standing Committee of the Standing Committee of the Shenzhen Municipal People's Congress said that the ban on private slaughter and related transactions, the standardized cold chain distribution and the quality and safety level of raw animal food can reduce the inappropriate contact between wild animals and humans and effectively prevent the spread of diseases.
